    <svcman/>
    <svcsubsec id="x08290182">
        <title>FUEL HEATER</title>
        <svcproc svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="0">
            <title>Circuit Functions</title>
            <para>The fuel heater is mounted in the fuel filter. It prevents fuel from gelling in the unfiltered side of
                the filter during cold weather.
            </para>
            <para>The system consists of a fuel heater relay, filter heating element, and a normally open thermoswitch.
                The switch closes at approximately 10&#176;C/50&#176;F.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
    </svcsubsec>
